description: Beijer Electronics Group AB engages in the development and distribution of industrial automation and communications solutions. The company is headquartered in Malmo, Skane and currently employs 769 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2000-06-08. The firm is active in three principal business areas: Automation, Human Machine Interface (HMI) Products and Industrial Data Communications (IDC). The Automation division delivers a range of products and solutions for automation in the Nordic and Baltic markets. This offering consists of control systems, drive systems, operator systems and components. The HMI Products division is engaged in the development and manufacture of human-machine interface systems, including operator terminals, monitors and keyboards. The IDC division develops, produces, markets and sells industrial data communication products. The firm operates worldwide, with sales units in 19 countries and development centers in Europe, Asia and the United States.
name: Beijer Electronics Group AB
